“We knew that the property values in my neighborhood were low,” he says of the area around 69th and Dorchester. “And none of us knew about whether or not those values would ever change. Friends of mine who had money sense would say, ‘Don’t invest all your money in this building ‘cause you’re never gonna get your money out of it.’ I wasn’t worried about or concerned about resale value, I was investing in my life. I was investing in my block.”